<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>If the federal funds rate is below the discount rate, banks will typically:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Borrow from the Federal Reserve</option>
            <option letter="b">Borrow from other banks</option>
            <option letter="c">Stop lending completely</option>
            <option letter="d">Increase their reserve requirements</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>When the federal funds rate (the rate banks charge each other) is lower than the discount rate (the rate the Fed charges), banks will prefer to borrow from other banks rather than from the Fed. This is why the discount rate is typically kept higher than the federal funds rate.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
